\pard\plain \s4\qj \f16 {Skeletons\par 
}\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 \tab Skeletons created by necromancy are fleshless remains of humanoids animated by {magick}ally-bound spirits.{ }
Skeletons are more mobile and agile because of their slight structure, but that are also relatively weak and delicate.{ }Skeletons created by the {\i animate lesser skeleton}{ r}itual (see page ??) are an
imated only for brief periods, since the spirit is bound to the remains only temporarily.{ }Since their spirits are bound to their remains indefinitely, greater skeletons remain animated for much longer periods.{ Otherwise}
, lesser and greater skeletons are identical in profile and abilities.\par 
\tab Special Rules:{ }Skeletons sense life at a range of six yards.{ }Skeletons are immune to psychology rules, and cannot be forced to leave combat.{ }They cause fear in living creatures.{ }A creature wounded by a skeleton has
 a 35% chance of contracting infected wounds (see {\ul WFRP}, page 83).\par 
