\pard\plain \s4\qj \f16 {Wraith}\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 \tab See {\ul WFRP}, page 253.{ }Wraiths are aethyrial spirits of dead Khaine worshippers returned to the Material Realm by Khaine to serve him in his war against the followers of Morr. \par 
\par 
\pard\plain \s4\qj \f16 {Carrion}\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 \tab See {\ul WFRP}, page 248.{ }Carrion are unique daemon-like undead flying creatures of the shadowrealm of the Death God Khaine, given by Khaine to favored servants as mounts.\par 
\par 
\pard\plain \s4\qj \f16 {Ghouls}\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 \tab See {\ul WFRP}, page 248.{ }Ghouls are living servants of the Death God Khaine who have surrendered themselves voluntarily to possession by morbid otherworldly spirits from Khaine\rquote s shadowrealm whose unho
ly mission is to ritually desecrate the graves and remains of the righteous dead protected by the god Morr.\par 
\par 
\pard\plain \s4\qj \f16 {Vampires}\par 
\pard\plain \qj \f16\fs20 \tab See {\ul WFRP}, page 250.{ }Vampires are believed to be the products of a secret variant of the {\i lichelife} ritual, probably of 2nd Millenium Dark Elven origin.{ }
These quasi-immortal beings are said to live in secret among the various cultures of the Old World, sometimes in small secret societies, sometimes as isolated hermits.\par 
